{
  "title": "AD #3 · Cultural Globalization (Path A · Agree)",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "我的观点是：文化全球化本身既不好也不坏。",
      "phrases": ["My view is that", "cultural globalization is not good or bad", "by itself."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "本地传统从中获益还是受损，取决于一件事：当这个文化被写进全球故事时，是自己还握着笔，还是别人替它在写？",
      "phrases": ["Whether a local tradition", "gains or loses from it", "depends on one thing:", "does that culture", "still hold the pen", "when it is written", "into the global story,", "or is someone else", "writing it for them?"]
    },
    {
      "translation": "当一个文化还掌着舵时，全球化让它更强而非更弱。",
      "phrases": ["When a culture", "stays in charge,", "globalization makes it stronger,", "not weaker."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "韩国电影先从好莱坞吸收理念，然后输出《寄生虫》和《鱿鱼游戏》。",
      "phrases": ["Korean films", "first took in ideas", "from Hollywood", "and then sent out", "Parasite and Squid Game."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "日本料理走向世界的同时，本土寿司也在不断生长、演变。",
      "phrases": ["Japanese food", "traveled around the world", "while sushi at home", "kept growing and changing."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这两例中，更多人认识了这些传统，而本地厨师和导演正是塑造外人看法的那些人。",
      "phrases": ["In both cases,", "more people now know", "these traditions,", "and local chefs and directors", "were the ones shaping", "how outsiders saw them."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这就是 Andrew 描绘的乐观画面。",
      "phrases": ["This is the happy picture", "Andrew paints."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "Kelly 的警告也是真实的，但发生在另一类情境里。",
      "phrases": ["Kelly's warning is also real,", "but it happens", "in a different kind of case."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "当一个小语言没有电视、学校、市场支撑时，接触更大的语言就等于被替代掉了。",
      "phrases": ["When a small language", "has no TV, no schools,", "and no market behind it,", "exposure to a bigger language", "simply replaces it."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "安达曼原住民语言就这样失去了阵地。",
      "phrases": ["Indigenous Andaman speech", "lost ground this way."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "失去不是交流本身造成的，而是讲故事权的不平等匹配造成的。",
      "phrases": ["The loss was not caused", "by exchange itself,", "but by an unequal match", "in who got to do the telling."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "所以真正该问的不是开放还是封闭，而是笔握在谁手里。",
      "phrases": ["So the right question", "is not open or close,", "but who holds the pen."]
    }
  ]
}
